Pre-heat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Pat the @chicken thigh{4} skin dry with some #kitchen paper{} and rub a knob of @butter{} or @olive oil{} on each thigh. Rub in a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and sprinkle over half the leaves from your @thyme{4}.

Cook them in your oven on the top shelf for ~{25%minutes}, until the skin is nice and crispy. Rest out of your oven afterwards.

> The chicken is fully cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Peel and finely chop the @carrot{1} and @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Finely chop the @celery stick{1} and remove the ends from the @green beans{1}(top and tailed). Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2} and drain and rinse the @green lentils{1}.

Add a splash of @olive oil{} to a #non-stick frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When your oil is hot, cook the @British smoked bacon lardons{1} until it is crispy around the edges. Remove your pancetta from the pan and keep it to the side for later.

Heat another dash of @olive oil{} in the same pan you cooked your pancetta in and turn the heat to medium-low. Add your carrot, onion, celery, @bay leaf{1} and your remaining thyme leaves. After about ~{5%minutes} your veggies should be nice and soft. Now boil a #pot{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for the green beans.

Add your pancetta and lentils to the pan with your veggies. Mix together and season with a couple of pinches of salt and pepper. Turn off the heat.

> Taste the mixture and add more seasoning if you need to.

Cook your green beans for ~{4%minutes} in the boiling water. Drain them and then immediately run them under cold water.

> This is to stop them cooking (i.e. 'refresh' them).